@Reasoning:
VOLUME accepts an arbitrary number of mount-point paths in a single
instruction. The HIR encoding wraps them as one Array argument so the
empty-list case is representable (caller intent: declare zero volumes is
ill-formed; the parser still emits one Array to keep arity uniform).
@End Reasoning

