@Reasoning:
ARG declares a build-time variable, optionally with a default. The arity-
2 contract pairs the name with a possibly empty default; the formatter
distinguishes "no default" from "empty default" via downstream conventions
since both can be represented by the empty string at this layer.
@End Reasoning

