@Reasoning:
ONBUILD wraps another instruction that fires when this image is used as a
base. The nested instruction is itself a HIR call, so this translator
recurses through translate_hir_call — the only translate_*_call in this
file that does so. Nesting depth is bounded because ONBUILD-of-ONBUILD is
forbidden by Docker, but the recursion is unguarded here on purpose
(any nesting violation is the upstream validator's responsibility).
@End Reasoning

