@Reasoning:
HEALTHCHECK NONE explicitly disables any inherited healthcheck from the
base image. It carries no parameters but still allocates the full 88-byte
HealthcheckInstruction record so the formatter can use a single emission
path keyed on is_none (offset 8). Zero-filling the unused fields keeps
the record well-defined for later debug-dumps.
@End Reasoning

Process called "translate_healthcheck_none_call" that takes backend_ptr as Integer, hir_call_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Translate dockerfile_healthcheck_none HIR call back to HEALTHCHECK NONE instruction AST.
    Arguments: (none)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Create HealthcheckInstruction AST node with is_none flag set.
    @End Implementation

    Let line be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_call_ptr, 8
    Let col be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_call_ptr, 16

    Note: Create HealthcheckInstruction node (NONE variant)
    Let healthcheck_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 88
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 0, DockerfileParser.NODE_HEALTHCHECK
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 8, 1  Note: is_none = 1
    proc memory_set_string from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 16, ""  Note: interval
    proc memory_set_string from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 24, ""  Note: timeout
    proc memory_set_string from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 32, ""  Note: start_period
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 40, 0  Note: retries
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 48, DockerfileParser.SHELL_FORM
    proc memory_set_string from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 56, ""  Note: cmd_command
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 64, 0  Note: cmd_args
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 72, line
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with healthcheck_ptr, 80, col

    Return healthcheck_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
HEALTHCHECK CMD packs every probe knob into a flat 7-tuple: three duration
strings (interval, timeout, start_period) kept as strings to preserve
"30s"/"1m" surface units, an int retries count, the shell-vs-exec form
flag, the shell command, and the exec args array. Empty duration strings
encode "use Docker default" — no separate optional flag needed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
88-byte HealthcheckInstruction record shared with the NONE variant; is_none
(offset 8) is 0 here. cmd_form (offset 48) discriminates SHELL_FORM vs
EXEC_FORM and selects which of cmd_command/cmd_args is meaningful.
@End Implementation

